00:04:39.210 --> 00:04:41.680
I really, really appreciate it.

00:04:41.680 --> 00:04:45.260
The group with whom I
work here at the Library

00:04:45.260 --> 00:04:48.740
of Congress is the National
Library Service for the Blind

00:04:48.740 --> 00:04:50.920
and Physically Handicapped.

00:04:50.920 --> 00:04:54.050
We refer to it as NLS because
we have quite a long name.

00:04:54.050 --> 00:05:00.170
NLS began in 1931 to
serve specifically adult

00:05:00.170 --> 00:05:01.470
who were blind.

00:05:01.470 --> 00:05:05.020
Over a period of time, over,
you know, the more than 85 years

00:05:05.020 --> 00:05:07.710
that we've been around,
we've evolved our services

00:05:07.710 --> 00:05:09.720
over a period of time
to reach a larger

00:05:09.720 --> 00:05:12.890
and larger group of people.

00:05:12.890 --> 00:05:20.790
So we serve people who are both
blind and visually impaired,

00:05:20.790 --> 00:05:24.760
people who have physical
disabilities that prevent them

00:05:24.760 --> 00:05:28.610
from being able to hold a book.

00:05:28.610 --> 00:05:35.790
And to a lesser extent, we serve
individuals who have dyslexia

00:05:35.790 --> 00:05:41.160
and other issues that may
prevent having accessibility

00:05:41.160 --> 00:05:45.540
to regular print materials.

00:05:45.540 --> 00:05:51.000
NLS serves people through
absolute spectacular network

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:57.300
of libraries around the country,
every state, Guam, Puerto Rico,

00:05:57.300 --> 00:06:03.640
who-- to whom we serve by
providing them with materials.

00:06:03.640 --> 00:06:08.580
So the types of materials
that we provide are braille,

00:06:08.580 --> 00:06:11.150
e-braille, audio books, and then

00:06:11.150 --> 00:06:16.540
of course we do have a download
service which is of course

00:06:16.540 --> 00:06:19.090
in keeping with-- how a lot

00:06:19.090 --> 00:06:23.210
of people are accessing
materials right now.

00:06:23.210 --> 00:06:28.370
In addition to books, which of
course there's a lot of ways

00:06:28.370 --> 00:06:34.800
that you can get audio books,
but we also provide magazines,

00:06:34.800 --> 00:06:38.100
guides, things that you
wouldn't necessarily think

00:06:38.100 --> 00:06:42.270
of for individuals who have
trouble reading print materials,

00:06:42.270 --> 00:06:47.280
things like tax guides,
nutrition guides,

00:06:47.280 --> 00:06:48.580
and so on and so forth.

00:06:48.580 --> 00:06:53.910
So that puts us in a position
of being somewhat unique.

00:06:53.910 --> 00:06:56.940
We're very proud
of our collection,

00:06:56.940 --> 00:06:58.840
which at this point is hundreds

00:06:58.840 --> 00:07:02.280
of thousands, over
200,000 pieces.

00:07:02.280 --> 00:07:08.750
We also provide music scores and
music instructional materials

00:07:08.750 --> 00:07:10.050
and so on and so forth.

00:07:10.050 --> 00:07:17.900
So we're trying to fill-- think
of void where we want to take

00:07:17.900 --> 00:07:19.740
into consideration that
there's a lot of people

00:07:19.740 --> 00:07:24.350
that just have trouble
with what's available

00:07:24.350 --> 00:07:28.810
from a print perspective, and
so we're constantly looking

00:07:28.810 --> 00:07:33.830
at where does need exists and
then trying to address them.

00:07:33.830 --> 00:07:38.990
Increasingly, the
individuals that we're serving

00:07:38.990 --> 00:07:41.960
with aging [inaudible] and
so on and so forth are people

00:07:41.960 --> 00:07:45.850
who may not have been
blind their entire life

00:07:45.850 --> 00:07:48.480
but have decreasing
capacity seeing.

00:07:48.480 --> 00:07:52.790
So we know that that
number is going up.

00:07:52.790 --> 00:07:55.820
And recently we have been--

00:07:55.820 --> 00:08:00.660
we've launched a pretty
extensive outreach campaign

00:08:00.660 --> 00:08:03.220
to make sure that people
are aware of these services

00:08:03.220 --> 00:08:04.870
because they are provided free.

00:08:04.870 --> 00:08:11.340
And we want to make sure
that people can read.

